{"id": "duc04-testb-0:8#25", "contents": "Slepian's friends and family remembered him as a man who cherished his time with loved ones. He had planned a cruise for the upcoming spring and had purchased a time-share apartment near Disney World in Florida. His wife, Lynne, recalled that he often joked about his own mortality, even teaching their African parrot his eulogy. Despite these lighthearted moments, Slepian's death was a devastating blow to those who knew him. As one friend noted, \"He wasn't done living yet.\""}
